From 7c76625089d282fd20829338c175090116d4d9f4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Slick <slick@slicksync.local>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 19:21:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: trace library fetch and gate evaluation for stuck items

v1.9.30 confirmed the scheduler runs healthily every minute, but a
fresh Nuvio checkpoint (~5min old, within the freshness window)
still wasn't reaching WatchSession despite multiple complete cycles
running after it appeared - a gap in the existing heartbeats, since
getLibraryForUser's live-fetch failure is caught internally and
wouldn't surface as a cycle-level failure.

Added heartbeats: whether the live Nuvio fetch succeeds vs silently
falling back to stale cache (and whether the target item is present
in what came back), plus tracing tt37287335 specifically through
sessionTracker's hasWatchProgress and isActivelyWatching gates to
find the exact point a genuinely fresh signal stops producing a
session.

Bump to 1.9.31, changelog entry added.
---
 client/public/changelog.json    | 10 ++++++++++
 package.json                    |  2 +-
 server/utils/activityMonitor.js | 10 ++++++++++
 server/utils/sessionTracker.js  | 28 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 4 files changed, 49 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

